    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-19T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="9"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.3335/22</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Stimson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-19T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>It is desired by this Government that visit of fleet to Argentina under command
                    Admiral Caperton should be so arranged that any genuine wishes of Argentine
                    Government may be fulfilled. You are therefore instructed, in view of above, to
                    arrange dates of functions to be attended by officers on their visit to Buenos
                    Aires, in such a manner that length of stay of vessels in Argentine ports shall
                    not exceed two weeks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
